<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is true (entailment) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: The newspaper publishes just one letter a week from a reader, always with an editorial riposte at the bottom. 
Statement: There are many letters submitted each week, but only one is chosen. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. Newspaper receives numerous letters from readers every week.
2. Only a single letter is published from the submitted ones.
3. Editorial response follows every selected letter.
4. A weekly letter selection process occurs in the newspaper.
5. High volume of letters received limits publication to one per week.
6. Letters not chosen are not published.
7. Editorial staff makes a weekly decision on which letter to publish.
8. Letters published are followed by the newspaper's response.
9. High submission rate of letters ensures a variety of choices.
10. The newspaper maintains a consistent format of one letter and an editorial riposte per issue.</s>